questions.explanation:
The cervical spine is the most commonly injured part of the spinal cord. The cervical spine accounts for 2/3rd of adult spine injuries. The most common part of the spine 
to be injured is the upper cervical vertebrae (C1–C4). The order of frequency of injury to the spinal cord is cervical &gt; thoracolumbar &gt; lumbar &gt; 
thoracic &gt; sacral level.
